# GitHub MCP Server - Environment Variables
#
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: This file is ONLY used for local development!
#
# Production environments do NOT use this file:
#   - Docker: Environment variables passed via -e flag
#   - peta-core: Environment variables passed via launchConfig.env
#   - Claude Desktop: Environment variables passed via config file
#
# To use this file for local development:
#   1. Copy this file to .env (already in .gitignore)
#   2. Fill in your GitHub access token
#   3. Run: npm run dev  OR  node dist/stdio.js
#
# =============================================================================
# AUTHENTICATION (Local Development Only)
# =============================================================================

# GitHub OAuth access token or Personal Access Token
#
# Token formats:
#   - Personal Access Token (classic): ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxx (40 chars)
#   - Fine-grained PAT: github_pat_xxxxxxxxxxxx
#   - OAuth access token: gho_xxxxxxxxxxxx
#   - GitHub App token: ghs_xxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# Get your token from:
#   Personal Access Token: https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   OAuth App: Implement OAuth flow in your application
#
# accessToken=ghp_YOUR_GITHUB_TOKEN_HERE
#
# Note: In production, peta-core handles token refresh automatically
#       via MCP notification (notifications/token/update)

# Required scopes for Personal Access Token:
#   - repo (Full control of private repositories)
#   - read:user (Read user profile data)
#   - user:email (Access user email addresses - optional)

# =============================================================================
# LOGGING
# =============================================================================

# Log level: DEBUG | INFO | WARN | ERROR | NONE
# Default: DEBUG in development, INFO in production
#
# Note: In STDIO mode, all logs are automatically written to stderr
#       to avoid polluting stdout (which is used for JSON-RPC)
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# =============================================================================
# GITHUB API CONFIGURATION (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# GitHub API base URL (default: https://api.github.com)
# Only change this if you're using GitHub Enterprise Server
# GITHUB_API_URL=https://api.github.com

# API request timeout in milliseconds (default: 30000)
# GITHUB_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# =============================================================================
# PROXY CONFIGURATION (Optional)
# =============================================================================

# If your network requires a proxy to access GitHub APIs, configure it here
# HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7897
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7897
# NO_PROXY=localhost,127.0.0.1
